members  of  militias  or  volunteer  corps  forming  part  of  such  armed
forces;

(1) Members  of  the  armed  forces  of  a  Party  to  the  conflict  as  well  as
members  of  militias  or  volunteer  corps  forming  part  of  such  armed
forces;

(a) correspondence,  lists  and  reports  exchanged  between  the  Central
Information Agency referred to in Article 123 and the National Bureaux
referred  to  in  Article  122;

(1) surname  and  first  names  of  the  prisoner  of  war,  his  rank,  his  army,
regimental, personal or serial number, his date of birth, and his profession
or  trade,  if  any;

(2) a summarised report of any preliminary investigation and of the trial,
emphasising  in  particular  the  elements  of  the  prosecution  and  the
defence;

(2) wounded and sick who, according to medical opinion, are not likely
to  recover  within  one  year,  whose  condition  requires  treatment  and
whose mental or physical fitness seems to have been gravely diminished;

(4) if  they  reside  in  an  area  particularly  exposed  to  the  dangers  of  war,
they  shall  be  authorized  to  move  from  that  area  to  the  same  extent
as  the  nationals  of  the  State  concerned;

(a) correspondence,  lists  and  reports  exchanged  between  the  Central
Information Agency referred to in Article 140 and the National Bureaux
referred  to  in  Article  136;

